# Argus

Argus is a React Native streaming hub: one UI over many providers (Netflix, Prime Video, NHL, etc.) via plugins. Support movies, series, and live events. Plugins come from public and private repositories (Kodi-like).

## Status

Implementation has begun (Phase 2). The plugin contract is real code in the `argus-plugin-sdk` repo, published to npm as `@argus-tv/plugin-sdk`. The host app (`argus`) is an Expo SDK 57 TV scaffold (`with-router-tv` + `react-native-tvos`). Prefer ADRs and `docs/` over inventing new plugin-runtime behavior.

## Keep living docs updated (non-negotiable)

Whenever you make a change that affects them, update these docs **in the same change, without being asked**:

- `docs/IMPLEMENTATION-PLAN.md` — check off / add tasks, update the status snapshot (phase, last updated, next milestone, blockers), decision log, and risk register.
- `docs/ARCHITECTURE.md` — reflect any design change; when a `(default)` becomes decided, update it and add/link an ADR in `docs/adr/`.
- `docs/PACKAGING.md` — reflect any build/distribution/CI change.
- `README.md` docs table + `AGENTS.md` — keep links and norms current when docs are added or moved.

The user should never have to ask for a doc update. If code and docs disagree, treat it as a bug and fix the docs.

## Constraints

- Keep core provider-agnostic; provider logic belongs in plugins.
- Do not implement scraping, reverse engineering, or credential circumvention for commercial services.
- Plugin runtime and code layout are decided (see `docs/adr/`): in-process TS-interface plugins ([ADR 0001](docs/adr/0001-plugin-contract-ts-interfaces.md)); multi-repo from day one ([ADR 0002](docs/adr/0002-multi-repo-layout.md)). Sandbox and DRM path remain open—see `docs/PLUGIN-SYSTEM.md`.
- Releasing the SDK is automated: add a **changeset**, push to `main`, merge the auto-generated "Version Packages" PR to publish `@argus-tv/plugin-sdk` (never hand-edit the version or run `npm publish`). See `argus-plugin-sdk/AGENTS.md` and `docs/PACKAGING.md`.
- Follow phases in `docs/DEVELOPMENT.md`. Read `AGENTS.md` for agent norms.
